main event: On June 8, 1961, a ground radar tracked a circular object with lights moving rapidly across the sky in Wisconsin Dells.
interesting points: The object was tracked at 5000 feet and traveled in a southerly direction., The object was tracked for approximately 6 minutes before disappearing from radar., Witnesses described additional sightings of circular and elongated objects in the area around the same date., No further information or details were gathered from additional witnesses during this report., Other reports included various shapes of observed UFOs, including cylindrical and oval forms.
witness description: an observer of flight operations at a nearby airport
